The paper deals with sparse signal and system identification, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of projections and convex sets suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The focus on signal processing and system identification suggests that the paper may also belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SP) or Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the use of adaptive algorithms and the comparison with the LASSO algorithm suggests that the paper may belong to the Statistical Learning (cs.SI) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.LG, followed by cs.SI, cs.SP, and cs.NA.
